DESCRIPTION:Contact Name: Laura Aunan<br>Contact Email: laura.aunan@esd.
 wa.gov<br>Workshop Language Option: English<br>Additional Information: <
 p>Please go to <a href="http://www.worksourcewa.com" target="_blank">Wor
 kSourceWA.com</a> and create your account prior to attending this worksh
 op.\n\nVideo conferencing will use a large portion of bandwidth and data
 . Before signing up\, be sure you have a data plan or reliable Wi-Fi acc
 ess that can accommodate this. To attend the workshop\, you are encourag
 ed to use a device capable of viewing video\, content and have audio cap
 ability. There is a call-in feature\, if you cannot log in virtually.\n
 \nA waitlist option will be enabled for this event. This waitlist is auto
 mated and if an attendee drops their registration\, the next registrant 
 on the waitlist will be invited. Each workshop requires a separate regis
 tration.\nWhen you sign up for this event\, please use the same name and
  email address that you use with your worksourcewa.com account\, if poss
 ible.\n\nContact the facilitator listed above in the contact lines for a
 ny additional questions or changes.\n\nIf you need an accommodation to p
 articipate in this training\, please contact the facilitators for this w
 orkshop. Please provide your name\, accommodation request\, and your tow
 n/city of residence. Please make your accommodation request as early as 
 possible so arrangements can be made.</p>\n\n&nbsp\;<br>Event Registrati
 on: Sign Up Required<br>Approved Unemployment Insurance (UI) Job Search 
 Activity: Yes<br><br><p>The Self&#8208\;Employment Assistance Program (S
 EAP) may be a great opportunity if you want to start a business!<br><br>
 Once approved\, SEAP is a unique program that enables you to:<br>&#183\;
  Receive entrepreneurial counseling and business coaching through a pre&
 #8208\;approved training provider<br>&#183\; Continue to collect Unemplo
 yment Insurance (UI) benefits while developing your business plans<br>&#
 183\; Work on creating your business and waives the weekly work&#8208\;s
 earch requirement<br><br>You are invited to attend a virtual workshop to
  explore:<br>&#8226\; What is SEAP? What does SEAP not do?<br>&#8226\; P
 rogram eligibility requirements and deadlines &#8226\; Locate and downlo
 ad from the SEAP Approved Provider List<br>&#8226\; What are the respons
 ibilities of an approved training provider?<br>&#8226\; Research the pro
 per training on the SEAP Approved Provider List<br>&#8226\; Frequently a
 sked questions (FAQ)<br>&#8226\; How to properly complete and submit the
  SEAP Application<br>&#8226\; Certification of Satisfactory Progress<br>
 &#8226\; Your responsibilities while enrolled in SEAP and to remain elig
 ible<br>&#8226\; Job Search Requirements\, WorkSource offices\, and cont
 act information<br><br>For further information\, contact Laura Aunan at 
 <a href="mailto:laura.aunan@esd.wa.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">l
 aura.aunan@esd.wa.gov</a></p>
CATEGORIES:WorkSource Downtown Seattle
